[1] VA: Rabid Raccoon in Richmond
Date: 26 Jun 2010
Source: WTVR.com [edited]
<http://www.wtvr.com/news/wtvr-rabid-racoon,0,4460848.story>


Richmond Police are advising residents in the Broad Rock area to be on
the lookout for a rabid raccoon.

Police tell CBS 6 that several residents in the 2800 block of Broad
Rock Blvd. called in Saturday [26 Jun 2010] morning to report
sightings of a raccoon that appeared to show signs of having rabies.
Police and animal control officers are searching for the animal and
advise that the animal could be hostile if it is indeed infected.

[Byline Travis Ponton]

