[2] SC: Rabies Warning for Beaufort Co. Residents
Date: 27 Jun 2010
Source: Island Packet.com [edited]
<http://www.islandpacket.com/2010/06/27/1289132/rabies-warning-issued-after-man.html>


A Hilton Head Island man was bitten by a rabid raccoon earlier this
month [June 2010], and state officials are warning Beaufort County
residents to be aware of the danger of rabies and reminding them to
vaccinate their pets.

The incident occurred 16 Jun 2010 when the man tried to break up a
fight between the raccoon and a dog, according to Sue Ferguson of the
S.C. Department of Health and Environmental Control (DHEC).

The raccoon later tested positive for rabies. It was the 3rd rabid
animal discovered in Beaufort County in 2010, according to a DHEC news
release. A rabid raccoon was discovered in March 2010 near the town of
Port Royal and city of Beaufort border, and another was found in April
2010 within Port Royal's town limits.

In 2009, there were 152 confirmed cases of rabies in animals in South
Carolina.
So far this year [2010], there have been 44 confirmed cases in animals
in the state.

