[6] VT: Aggressive fox in Barre City
Date: 3 Jul 2010
Source Burlington Free Press [edited]
<http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/article/20100703/NEWS02/7030311/Fox-death-in-Barre-City-leads-to-rabies-alert>


A "physical encounter" between a Barre City resident and a gray fox
Thursday [3 Jul 2010] and the location Friday of a dead gray fox in
the same area have led authorities to renew rabies warnings, according
to a Barre City Police Department report.

The dead fox, which might have been the animal that exhibited
aggressive behavior Thursday [3 Jul 2010] is being sent to a
laboratory to be tested for rabies, the report states. No injuries
came from the human-fox encounter, police added.

Visitors to the Barre City Pool and playground area and residents of
adjacent neighborhoods are urged to call Vermont State Police at
229-9191 to report any foxes behaving strangely.

Read more at
<http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/article/20100703/NEWS02/7030311/Fox-death-in-Barre-City-leads-to-rabies-alert#ixzz0sePtvrbm>.

