[7] NC: Rabid Fox fights with 2 unvaccinated dogs and bites person
Date: 2 Jul 2010
Source: The Dispatch [edited]
<http://www.the-dispatch.com/article/20100702/ARTICLES/100709983/1005>


A rabid fox was found Wednesday [30 Jun 2010] in the Hasty community.
The fox was in a fight with 2 dogs and bit a person. Neither dog was
properly vaccinated, and both have been euthanized. The person was
referred to a physician for medical follow-up.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[Rabies can affect any mammal. Any domestic mammal having contact with
humans, including horses, should be vaccinated against rabies.

If an animal is out of its usual habitat, such as a bat in your house
or a fox in your yard in the city, you should be especially wary of
touching these animals.

Rabies is a deadly viral disease in almost all cases. There are
vaccinations for pets, and for people at risk, such as veterinarians,
there are rabies vaccines for humans as well. There is also a post
exposure prophylaxis vaccine for exposed humans. Sadly, if our pets
are not vaccinated, they are usually put to death by a humane method,
but it is still an emotional trauma that can be avoided. - Mod.TG]
